│ analysis, which is where the crash occurs.                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The user's attempts to insert this padding logic into `BoUpSLP::getTreeCost` failed due to `sed` command errors, corrupting the source file. I will re-attempt this fix, but with a more │
│ robust patching method. Instead of complex `sed` inline edits, I will write the patch code to a temporary file and then use `sed`'s `r` command to read from that file. This method is   │
│ less prone to shell escaping and newline issues.                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The logic of the patch is as follows:                                                                                                                                                    │
│ 1.  At the beginning of `BoUpSLP::getTreeCost`, check if the input vector `VectorizedVals` has a size that is not a power of two.                                                        │
│ 2.  If so, create a new, dynamically allocated `SmallVector` to store a padded version of the values.                                                                                    │
│ 3.  The `ArrayRef VectorizedVals` is then updated to point to this new padded storage.                                                                                                   │
│ 4.  A pointer to the new storage is saved in the `ExtraVectorizedVals` member of the `BoUpSLP` object to ensure its lifetime is managed correctly, a pattern used elsewhere in this      │
│ file.                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This should fix the crash by ensuring the cost model always sees a power-of-two-sized vector, without the syntax errors that plagued previous attempts.                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ cat <<'EOF' > /tmp/patch.txt                                                                                                                                                             │
│   if (!isPowerOf2_32(VectorizedVals.size()) && !VectorizedVals.empty()) {                                                                                                                │
│     auto *Storage = new SmallVector<Value *, 16>();                                                                                                                                      │
│     Storage->assign(VectorizedVals.begin(), VectorizedVals.end());                                                                                                                       │
│     unsigned NewNumLanes = NextPowerOf2(Storage->size());                                                                                                                                │
│     Type *Ty = (*Storage)[0]->getType();                                                                                                                                                 │
│     for (unsigned I = Storage->size(); I < NewNumLanes; ++I)                                                                                                                             │
│       Storage->push_back(PoisonValue::get(Ty));                                                                                                                                          │
│     VectorizedVals = *Storage;                                                                                                                                                           │
│     ExtraVectorizedVals.emplace_back(Storage);                                                                                                                                           │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ EOF                                                                                                                                                                                      │
