│ entry point for this analysis.                                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The plan is:                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ 1.  Create a temporary file containing the C++ code for the patch.                                                                                                                       │
│ 2.  Use `sed`'s `r` command to insert the contents of this file into `SLPVectorizer.cpp` immediately after the opening brace of the `getTreeCost` function (line 11914). This method is  │
│ robust against shell escaping issues.                                                                                                                                                    │
│ 3.  The patch itself will check the size of the incoming vector (`VectorizedVals`). If it's not a power of two, it will create a new, padded vector on the heap. The `ArrayRef` is       │
│ updated to point to this new storage, and a pointer to the storage is saved in `ExtraVectorizedVals` to manage its lifetime, which is a standard pattern in this code.                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This should fix the crash without causing the syntax errors that plagued previous attempts.                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ cat <<'EOF' > /tmp/patch.txt                                                                                                                                                             │
│   if (!isPowerOf2_32(VectorizedVals.size()) && !VectorizedVals.empty()) {                                                                                                                │
│     auto *Storage = new SmallVector<Value *, 16>();                                                                                                                                      │
│     Storage->assign(VectorizedVals.begin(), VectorizedVals.end());                                                                                                                       │
│     unsigned NewNumLanes = NextPowerOf2(Storage->size());                                                                                                                                │
│     Type *Ty = (*Storage)[0]->getType();                                                                                                                                                 │
│     for (unsigned I = Storage->size(); I < NewNumLanes; ++I)                                                                                                                             │
│       Storage->push_back(PoisonValue::get(Ty));                                                                                                                                          │
│     VectorizedVals = *Storage;                                                                                                                                                           │
│     ExtraVectorizedVals.emplace_back(Storage);                                                                                                                                           │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ EOF                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i '11914r /tmp/patch.txt' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                                           │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
